title: TWINS2 - Spacecraft Ephemeris - D. McComas (Southwest Research Institute)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/twins/twins2/ephemeris/or/2008/twins2_or_def_20080411_v01.cdf. The most common cadence, 420000 [ms] = PT7M, occurred for 29.4118% of the 70 timesteps.

parameters.name: FSCECI_O
parameters.description: ---> (Orbit Plot). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['FSCECI']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
